    Open Notepad or any text editor.

    Copy and paste the following lines into the text editor:


@echo off
echo Setting Power Plan...
powercfg /S "Your Power Plan GUID"
echo Power Plan set successfully!

Replace "Your Power Plan GUID" with the actual GUID of your power plan.
You can find the GUID of your power plan
by running the following command in the Command Prompt:


powercfg /L



##EXAMPLE:

PS C:\Users\micha> powercfg /L

Existing Power Schemes (* Active)
-----------------------------------
Power Scheme GUID: 381b4222-f694-41f0-9685-ff5bb260df2e  (Balanced)
Power Scheme GUID: 5982fb10-41ea-4b6e-856d-103c2030e284  (Ultimate Performance)
Power Scheme GUID: 8c5e7fda-e8bf-4a96-9a85-a6e23a8c635c  (High performance) *
